      • getCaptchaId

        public String getCaptchaId(CaptchaService.CaptchaType ctype)
        Get a captcha ID. This may be used for the lifetime of an authentication process. It must stay the same between the challenge and verification process of the CAPTCHA.
        Parameters:
        ctype - the captcha type
        Returns:
        String.

      • isCaptchaSupportEnabled

        public boolean isCaptchaSupportEnabled()
        Get if CAPTCHA support is globally enabled. All CAPTCHA use should be disabled if this method returns false. Returning true does not necessarily enable all CAPTCHA use, other factors may come into play.
        Returns:
        true if CAPTCHA support is enabled, false if no CAPTCHA should be used.
